    ('SLAV-T 260', 'THE VAMPIRE IN EUROPEAN AND AMERICAN CULTURE', '14485', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 3:55 PM–5:10 PM', 'GA 0005', 'Jeffrey Holdeman', 0, NULL, 'Seminar', '3', 'GLOBAL & INTERNATIONAL STUDIES', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Explores the eastern European origins of the vampire and how the vampire in its look, nature, vulnerabilities, and threat has changed over the centuries, from premodern belief systems to European literature to cinema and games, to subcultures today.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd A&H credit
IUB GenEd World Culture credit
COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Global Civ & Culture'], NULL),
